nd Current Appointees)</span><hr size=1> This is a placeholder containing the Pull Team program description and current appointees.<br>
<br>
There are three core members of the Pull team, plus one rotational member taken from the membership of the KoF. The last two members of the pull team are situational, taken from those available and dependent on the pull technique required.<br>
<br>
A squad leader and 2 permanent members have been chosen from the volunteers by the Marshal of the March. These three core members will then decide on another volunteer who is not part of the core pull team, and work with them for a period of time (also decided by the pull team). After that time the squad leader will invite another KoF member to work with them. The idea is to get all those interested in the job a chance to work the leading edge of raids, and train folks on what the pull team is about so that there will be a better working knowledge within the guild on it's responsibilities and capabilities.<br>
<br>
General Responsibilities: <br>
Obviously, the pull team's main duty is to pull monsters for the KoF on our events. Focus on tactics and planning for this duty primarily, and teaching the general membership appropriate techniques secondarily. Fear no faction hits, and work on new techniques when standard pull tactics fail or fall short of potential.<br>
<br>
Consider yourself an asset of the KoF. This guild is your home, and will provide its resources and experience for your benefit. By volunteering for the pull team, you have committed to playing at least twice a week in an official event, unless:<br>
1. There is no official guild event that week.<br>
2. The official guild event does not give at least four days notice.<br>
3. Acts of God, real life issues, or server shut down cause you to be unable to play.<br>
<br>
Specific Responsibilities:<br>
Aerrenn Valorton, Squad Leader: Aerren, your responsibility is to do any required team management, and help ensure that the pull team is well-equipped to do their job. Work with the Marshal of the March (Charcoth) or the Sergeant of the Shield (Leare) to set up raids to obtain equipment for the pull team. You are to keep your team well-informed of tactics and zone intelligence for planned and possible future events. Keep track of who you work with and who you need to work with, assessing their strengths and weaknesses and working to help them improve. Mold the pull team into an effective unit; you are responsible for their safety. Stand willing to take less experienced players under your wing and help them refine their playing ability.<br>
<br>
Flaten and Loralis, Core Members: Your responsibility is to keep an open mind and always be willing to look for doing things better, faster, and with more style. Work to ensure that the pull team is able to do their job safely and efficiently. Help the membership of the KoF work with the pull team, and learn how best to work with the membership. Make the pull team into an effective unit. Stand willing to take less experienced players under your wing and help them refine their playing ability.<br>
